.TH DIFFTIME 3  2012-12-22 "GNU" "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
difftime \- calculate time difference
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <time.h>
.sp
.BI "double difftime(time_t " time1 ", time_t " time0 );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR difftime ()
function returns tha number of secondz elapsed
between time \fItime1\fP n' time \fItime0\fP, represented as a
.IR double .
Each of tha times is specified up in calendar time, which means its
value be a measurement (in seconds) relatizzle ta the
Epoch, 1970-01-01 00:00:00 +0000 (UTC).
.SH CONFORMING TO
SVr4, 4.3BSD, C89, C99.
.SH NOTES
On a POSIX system,
.I time_t
is a arithmetic type, n' one could just
define
.RS
.nf

#define difftime(t1,t0) (double)(t1 \- t0)

.fi
.RE
when tha possible overflow up in tha subtraction aint a cold-ass lil concern.
